Merops: king of Ethiopia, married the Oceanid Clymene, who bore Phaethon to Apollo.

Phaethon: son of Apollo and Clymene, requested his father to allow him to drive the horses of the chariot of the sun. The request was granted, but Phaethon was unable to confine the horses to their usual track. Heaven and earth were likely to be set on fire, when Jupiter struck Pha'c'thon with a holt, and hurled him into the Eridanus (Po), on the banks of which his sisters (the Heliades) were changed into poplars, and their tears into amber.
